HOUSE JOINT RESOLUTION 837
By Travis
A RESOLUTION to recognize Jim Vincent on the occasion of his
retirement.
WHEREAS, it is fitting that the members of this General Assembly should specially
recognize those citizens who have performed with uncommon devotion and enthusiasm
throughout their years of public service; and
WHEREAS, Jim Vincent is one such estimable individual, who has served for four years
as Rhea County Executive, from which position he is taking his retirement; and
WHEREAS, a dedicated professional, Mr. Vincent has faithfully served and executed the
duties of his office to produce strategic growth and ensure long-term sustainability for the county
through investments in infrastructure, education, commerce, and workforce development; and
WHEREAS, during his tenure, he has helped expand state-of-the-art fiber optic access
through partnerships with local utilities, secured land for the construction of a new Tennessee
College of Applied Technology (TCAT), and facilitated the expansion of water system
infrastructure; and
WHEREAS, Mr. Vincent also demonstrated his enduring commitment to serving the
citizens of Rhea County through his previous roles as a Rhea County Commissioner (2019-
2022) and as the State Representative for House District 31 during the 102nd and 103rd General
Assemblies (2001-2004); and
WHEREAS, Jim Vincent exemplifies the spirit and allegiance to family and community
that are characteristic of a true Tennessean; and
WHEREAS, throughout his illustrious tenure, Mr. Vincent has carried out his
responsibilities with diligence and integrity, and his remarkable success as a public servant and
civic leader cast the mold for all who will follow; and
HJR0837
012309
- 1 -

WHEREAS, a strong advocate for the citizens of Rhea County, Jim Vincent compiled a
singular record of success during his exemplary public service career, and he should be
specially recognized; now, therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES OF THE ONE HUNDRED
FOURTEENTH GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, THE SENATE
CONCURRING, that we honor and commend Jim Vincent for his honorable and astute service
to the people of Tennessee as Rhea County Executive and extend to him our best wishes for a
happy and fulfilling retirement.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that an appropriate copy of this resolution be prepared
for presentation with this final clause omitted from such copy and upon proper request made to
the appropriate clerk, the language appearing immediately following the State seal appear
without House or Senate designation.
